 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "DS-RENAME: Rename store.bin to checkpoint.bin — clarify semantics. store.bin currently serves as both a performance cache AND a shared mutable state (the source of the stale cache bug). Renaming to checkpoint.bin clarifies: it is a RECOVERY ARTIFACT, not a shared resource. Only the daemon writes it (at checkpoint time). Only the daemon reads it (at startup for recovery). The CLI never touches it when the daemon is running. In direct mode (no daemon), the CLI loads checkpoint.bin + replays .edn delta (same as daemon recovery). This rename is semantic — it changes no code behavior — but it prevents the mental model that led to the stale cache bug: 'store.bin is the cache that all processes share.' No. checkpoint.bin is the daemon's private recovery snapshot."
